==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hospitaler
<hw>Hos"pi*tal*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hospitaller</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[F. <ets>hospitalier</ets>. See
<er>Hospital</er>, and cf. <er>Hostler</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
residing in a hospital, for the purpose of receiving the poor, the sick,
and strangers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of an order of knights who built a hospital at
Jerusalem for pilgrims, <sc>A. D.</sc> 1042. They were called
<xex>Knights of St. John of Jerusalem</xex>, and after the removal of
the order to Malta, <xex>Knights of Malta</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hospitalization</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>hospitalisation</ent>⟦br⟧
